        "description": "## Overview\n[undici](https://www.npmjs.org/package/undici) is an An HTTP/1.1 client, written from scratch for Node.js\n\nAffected versions of this package are vulnerable to Allocation of Resources Without Limits or Throttling via the decompression chain. An attacker can cause high CPU usage and excessive memory allocation by sending HTTP responses with a large number of chained compression steps in the `Content-Encoding` header.\n## Remediation\nUpgrade `undici` to version 6.23.0, 7.18.2 or higher.\n## References\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/commit/b04e3cbb569c1596f86c108e9b52c79d8475dcb3)\n- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/commit/d3aafea7a2b3c351970c0c634b7cba8231763ca4)\n- [GitHub Release](https://github.com/nodejs/undici/releases/tag/v6.23.0)\n",
